doc.ContractDescription: IGF::OT::IGF HEEET HAS A SIGNED MOU AGREEMENT BETWEEN STMD, SMD AND NASA AMES TO MATURE AND DELIVER HEEET AT TRL 6 FOR POTENTIAL MISSION INFUSION BY FY17. THE HEEET TEAM IS CURRENTLY WORKING WITH A DISCOVERY PROPOSER WITH PROPOSALS DUE IN MID-FEB 2015. IN ADDITION, AN ESA M4 PROPOSAL WAS RECENTLY SUBMITTED THAT HAS BASELINED HEEET. THESE PROPOSALS REQUIRE HEEET TO BE AT TRL 6 BY FY17. A NUMBER OF NEW FRONTIERS PROPOSERS HAVE CONTACTED THE HEEET PROJECT EXPLORING USE OF HEEET IN THEIR PROPOSALS, IT IS ANTICIPATED THAT THE NEW FRONTIERS CALL WILL COME OUT IN FY16/17. FURTHER OUT, THERE ARE ADDITIONAL ESA-M5 PROPOSALS THAT ARE ALSO INTERESTED IN HEEET.IN ORDER TO BE FEASIBLE FOR MISSION INFUSION IN DISCOVERY-14, DISCOVERY-17, NF-4 OPPORTUNITIES AS WELL AS ESA M4 AND M5 MISSIONS, THE HEEET TECHNOLOGY MUST BE MATURED TO TRL 6 BY FY17 (END USER NEED DATE). IN ORDER TO ACHIEVE THESE LEVELS OF MATURITY THE TECHNOLOGY MUST BE DEVELOPED UTILIZING THICKER AND WIDER MATERIAL THAN IS CURRENTLY MANUFACTURABLE, THEREFORE REQUIRING AN INVESTMENT IN THE SCALE UP OF WEAVING CAPABILITY TO 2.1 THICKNESS X 24 WIDTH. THE WEAVING SCALE UP MUST BE COMPLETED BY EARLY Q2 FY16 TO MEET THE TRL 6 BY FY17 SCHEDULE. THE VENDOR WAS PUT UNDER CONTRACT IN Q2 FY14 AND IS CURRENTLY IN THE PROCESS OF UPGRADING THE WEAVING INFRASTRUCTURE TO SUPPORT THE WEAVING OF 12 WIDE MATERIAL. THIS REQUEST IS A STEP-UP FROM THE CURRENT CAPABILITY AND WILL UTILIZE MOST OF THE INFRASTRUCTURE IN PLACE FOR FURTHER EXTENSION TO 24 WIDE MATERIAL AND INCLUDES SET-UP AND WEAVING OF 24 WIDE MATERIAL TO DEMONSTRATE THE CAPABILITY.
